on logic works correctly.","test_description":"Populate a test KB with known entries (e.g., 'John joined in 2020', 'Budget is $50k'). Create drafts with contradictions ('John joined in 2019', 'Budget is $60k') and non-contradictions ('John leads the team'). Run the checker against real KB state and verify it flags only the contradictions. Test edge cases: synonym matching, negations, partial overlaps.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.35,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure mode is 'LLM hallucinates facts instead of including a disclaimer when KB is empty.' Mocking the KB to return empty results doesn't ensure the LLM actually generates a disclaimer—it might still confidently invent details. Only calling the real LLM with an empty/irrelevant KB can catch this hallucination behavior, which is inherent to LLM non-determinism and can't be simulated by a deterministic mock.","test_description":"Call the real LLM with an email context and an empty or irrelevant KB. Verify the generated draft includes explicit language like 'I don't have confirmed information about...' or 'Based on available records...'. Verify it does NOT confidently assert specific facts not mentioned in the KB. Run 5+ times; require 90%+ consistency on disclaimer inclusion.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure mode is code that accidentally sends without checking approval status. Mocking the approval flag to 'pending' hides bugs in the actual integration between approval state and the send function. You must test with real approval state storage (DB, cache, or in-process state) to catch off-by-one errors, race conditions, or forgotten approval checks.","test_description":"Set up a draft in the system with real approval state (pending, rejected, approved). Attempt to send with approval='pending' and verify send() fails or returns not-sent. Attempt with approval='rejected' and verify send is blocked. Attempt with approval='approved' and verify send succeeds. Do NOT mock the approval state; use real state storage. Test state transitions to catch missed checks.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior requires orchestrating multiple real systems in sequence: real email I/O → real LLM → fact-checking (possibly LLM-based) → real approval state → real send. Testing each step in isolation with mocks hides failures in data flow (e.g., draft format breaks the checker), sequencing (e.g., approval step is skipped), or timing. This is a full agentic pipeline where failures emerge from the interaction of multiple LLM and non-LLM steps, not from single-step bugs.","test_description":"Execute the entire pipeline: read a multi-point email thread, generate draft via real LLM, run fact-checking (real KB or LLM), verify draft is presented to user without auto-sending, reject approval once, verify no send, then approve and verify send succeeds. Use real email data (not mocked), real LLM, real KB/checker. Verify the thread context flows correctly through all steps and no step is skipped.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.8}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_seque